title: Scarhaven Keep
creator: J. S. Fletcher
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of Scarhaven Keep by J. S. Fletcher. Read by Cathy Barratt. The northern English sea coast provides a compelling backdrop for this genre of writing; a mysterious disappearance, a love interest, and plot twists 'se mijotent' to produce an intriguing read. (Summary by Cate Barratt) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B(206MB)
subject: murder; mystery; librivox

reviews.reviewbody: Thanks Cathy for a most enjoyable read.
reviews.reviewtitle: Another good yarn from JS Fletcher
